venice.lib.parser

Class XIORegExParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • venice.lib.parser.XIOParser
      • venice.lib.parser.XIORegExParser

  • public class XIORegExParser
extends XIOParser
    Parses strings to slotEvents and vice versa. Uses regular expression matching. Strings need to be in the format of a XIO line, for example:
    <sfstring value="hello world" timestamp="1394123456789" sensorname="messagebox"/>

    The order of the attributes in the XIO line may not be changed.

    Author:
    Oliver Eickmeyer

      • stringToEvent

        public SlotEvent stringToEvent(java.lang.String str)
        Parse a single string into a type timed event (TTE), string has to be in xml format:
        <type value="..." timestamp="..." sensorName="..."/>
        or the old format : <irio:type ...></irio:type>
        Examples:
        <sfint32 value="123" timestamp="1381234567890" sensorName="test"/>
        <irio:sfint32 value="123" timestamp="1381234567890" sensorName="test"></irio:sfint32>
        Overrides:
        stringToEvent in class XIOParser
        Parameters:
        str - The string that is to parsed.
        Returns:
        Returns always a TTE object. In case of a failed parsing attempt, a fail TTE is created.
